President Obama issued a statement honoring the passing of Lucy Coffey, a veteran who served in the Women's Army Auxiliary Corps during World War II. Coffey served with distinction in the Pacific theater and earned two bronze stars. After the war, she continued to serve as an Army civilian. Coffey's example has inspired generations of patriots. President Obama and Vice President Biden had the opportunity to meet Coffey at the White House last year, where they witnessed her unwavering love for her country. The statement concludes by expressing condolences to Coffey's family, friends, and loved ones.